[src:serde-rust/serialization] This is useful for sending a complex data structure over a network socket or storing it in a database.
[src:serde-rust/serialization] When serializing structures with `Storable`, there are network safe functions that always store their data in a format that is readable on any computer at a small cost of speed.
[src:serde-rust/serialization] These functions are named `nstore`, `nfreeze`, etc.
