[src:serde-rust/serialization] The `unserialize` function allows to read an object from a connection or a raw vector.
[src:serde-rust/serialization] REBOL will serialize to file (`save/all`) or to a `string!` (`mold/all`).
[src:serde-rust/serialization] Strings and files can be deserialized using the polymorphic `load` function.
[src:serde-rust/serialization] `RProtoBuf` provides cross-language data serialization in R, using Protocol Buffers.
[src:serde-rust/serialization] Ruby includes the standard module `Marshal` with 2 methods `dump` and `load`, akin to the standard Unix utilities `dump` and `restore`.
[src:serde-rust/serialization] These methods serialize to the standard class `String`, that is, they effectively become a sequence of bytes.
[src:serde-rust/serialization] Some objects cannot be serialized (doing so would raise a `TypeError` exception): bindings, procedure objects, instances of class IO, singleton objects and interfaces.
